# Visualization

```text
Before Processing:

[ 0s ][ 1s ][ Unsorted ][ 2s ]
        low
        mid
                     high
```

After every operation:

```text
0 ... low-1      -> 0s
low ... mid-1    -> 1s
mid ... high     -> Unknown
high+1 ... n-1   -> 2s
```

The range from `mid` to `high` is the **unsorted zone** we are scanning and fixing.

At each step:

* If `nums[mid] == 0`

  * Swap with `low`
  * Move `low` and `mid`

* If `nums[mid] == 1`

  * Just move `mid`

* If `nums[mid] == 2`

  * Swap with `high`
  * Move only `high`

---

# Complexity Comparison

| Approach            | Time | Space |
| ------------------- | ---- | ----- |
| Counting Sort       | O(n) | O(1)  |
| Dutch National Flag | O(n) | O(1)  |

---

# Interview One-Liner

**The Dutch National Flag Algorithm uses three pointers (`low`, `mid`, `high`) to partition the array into 0s, 1s, and 2s in a single traversal, achieving O(n) time and O(1) space.**
